      • addChangeListener

        public void addChangeListener(javax.swing.event.ChangeListener newListener)
        Description copied from interface: CachableObjectIF
        CachableObject supports ChangeListeners for convenience. The listeners are not stored persistently so in order to be sure to receive events, keep a reference to the object. CachableObjectHandles do not maintain a reference. The cache and GC may discard unreferenced objects at any time even if they have ChangeListeners attached and if the object is subsequently reloaded by the cache the ChangeListeners will not be reattached.
        Specified by:
        addChangeListener in interface CachableObjectIF<I>
